      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "So I have the impression that you think that previously \"bitcoind getrawtransaction\" worked without communication to another running bitcoind. This is not correct - such functionality never existing, and whenever you typed \"bitcoind [command]\", it always needed to find a running daemon to talk to. This did not change, only the ability to send commands elsewhere was moved from bitcoind to bitcoin-cli. \n\nHowever, very recently a new command was added (bitcoin-tx; not in a release yet), which allows for some simply offline transaction manipulation, without assistance from a bitcoind. It cannot manipulate your wallet though, just individual transactions.\n",
